Pet Pantries offers assistance to so many people in need. Daisy's Hope Foundation does a big one almost every month and provides pet food and other necessities to more than 300 families. No one should have to choose between feeding their animals or dumping them at a shelter. It takes a village, and we can all be of service to make our communities a better and healthier place for everyone.
These organizations rely on your donations. All of this is made possible through the kindness of others, and a huge team of volunteers. A very special thanks to @Fixnfidos @kaceymontoya @thelittleangelsproject for this wonderful donation of Science Diet dog and cat food.
#catsnippers #fixnfidos #littleangelsproject #Daisyshopefo

It takes a village! Thank you, Yvette, for helping fill the Daisy's Hope Foundation pet pantry with Science Diet dog and cat food. Donations are harder to come by these days, and we are so appreciative of those who go the distance to assist. Thank you, Kacey Montoya, for putting this together. Catsnippers is grateful for the non-profits that work together for the better good of their communities ❤

It is World Spay Day! 
Catsnippers is dedicated to
spaying and neutering cats and dogs to reduce the shelter population and keep animals in homes. Getting your
pets fixed will keep them from roaming, as well as protect them from certain cancers and other medical
issues. Have a heart, spay your furry friends as soon as possible.

#Catsnippers #worldspayday #spayandneutersaveslives #catsnippersla #adoptdontshop

We need shelter reform now! @mayorofla needs to hire a GM to tackle the tremendous issues plaguing our county's shelter system. Animals are languishing in their kennels and not getting the enrichment they need or timely medical care. Spay and neuter programs and municipal services are grossly lacking to serve our community. These animals need to be adopted out as quickly as possible.

Thank you to everyone who showed up today to demand change in the Los Angeles shelter system. We will not stop until @mayorofla Karen Bass appoints a new general manager to fix the shelter crisis. The city budget must  include ample staffing, extended shelter hours, more volunteers, resources, and most importantly-the ethical and humane treatment of all animals that enter the system. If you love animals, stand up and speak up. The animals can't wait.

Happy Crazy Cat Lady Day! My Catsnippers charity is almost a year old. Last year, I decided to focus on spay and neuter assistance in the Southern California area. My goal is to have a low-cost mobile unit, and I am fundraising to make that a reality. There are so many pet lovers out there that have no idea how many millions of animals are wasting away in shelters or on the streets because no one wants them. We can put an end to the needless suffering by spaying and neutering pets so that the population is reduced. Education is key. Please adopt your pets. Do not breed and buy when shelter pets die.

#spayandneuter #spayandneutersaveslives 
#adoptdontshop 
#catsnippers 
#Catsnipperla

Today's catch. Four dumped babies🥺
Kitten season brings a fresh hell every year, as so many cats are not altered and multiply out of control. There are literally thousands discarded like trash every day as people simply do not want them or care what happens. We need all the help we can get to have cats and dogs spayed, neutered, and vaccinated. Your donation to Catsnippers would mean the world to me, and so many others that desperately need help.
Link in bio. Or donate here: 
https://app.autobooks.co/pay/catsnippers-los-angeles

We are fundraising for our next Catsnippers spay and neuter clinic. If you love animals, please consider a donation of any size. 100% goes to the animals. We provide spay, neuter, vaccines and microchips
We are overloaded with cats, dogs, kittens and puppies in every area. Shelters are overwhelmed and overcrowded due to exploding populations. Please lend us your support and share this post. Without spay and neuter clinics, the amount of animals euthanized each month is staggering🥺
Please click the donate button on my page. You can make a difference you  by spaying, neutering, and adopting a pet.
